anyone know any conforming quotes henry david thoreau has some of the best ones if a man does not keep pace with his companions perhaps it is because he hears a different drummer let him step to the music which he hears however measured or far away every generation laughs at the old fashions but follows religiously the new i hear many condemn these men because they were so few when were the good and the brave ever in a majority there are also good quotes by others every society honors its live conformists and its dead troublemakers mignon mclaughlin don't think you're on the right road just because it s a well beaten path unknown whenever you find yourself on the side of the majority it is time to pause and reflect mark twain you laugh at me because i am different i laugh because you are all the same daniel knode Henry David Thoreau Joke Shania Twain Mark Twain Time Out of Mind Christian anarchism Drummer Punk ideology The Caves of Androzani Joy Division (band) Good Morning, Vietnam Anne Boleyn Mojave people Bah__'__ Faith and World Religions Donald Rumsfeld Marching band Ralph Waldo Emerson Parsifal Women in Islam Grateful Dead Quotation mark Pogo Kingdom Hearts: Chain of Memories Funeral Bitches Brew Slow Train Coming Infidels Battle of Perryville Beat generation The Smiths Hank Aaron Social rule Virginian Railway Literature of the United States Bugs Bunny Guns N' Roses History of Christianity and homosexuality Eternal Sunshine of the Spotless Mind Question (comics) David Crosby Zhao Yun I Want to Hold Your Hand Constitution of the Turkish Republic of Northern Cyprus References in Star Trek Simple living Doctor Wily International League Breath of Fire III Gettysburg Battlefield Killing Joke The Ashlee Simpson Show John McLaughlin (musician) Duel Hippie William N. Page Ten Commandments Building the Virginian Railway Rudyard Kipling Snare drum Blackfoot music Laugh track Minor characters in Morrowind Trainspotting (novel) Poetry of the United States Drum and bass Pa